=================================
Eisenstein & Hu Fitting functions
=================================

Power spectra for CDM variants with/without baryonic effects
=======================================================

C code
------

power.c and tf_fit.c are redistributed under the MIT License with the permission of
Wayne Hu

http://background.uchicago.edu/~whu/transfer/transferpage.html

and is described in Eisenstein, D. J., & Hu, W. "Power Spectra for
Cold Dark Matter and Its Variants," 1999, ApJ, 511, 5
[astro-ph/9710252]. Please cite this paper to acknowledge use of power
spectrum calculations.

See LICENSE file.


Python Interface
----------------

Interface generated using swig on the '.c' files:

eg:  $ swig -python power.i
 
distutils is then used to build the package from
setup.py, and place it in the current directory:

     $ python setup.py build_ext --inplace
